P4 labs worldwide (02) today
[1
Date: Thu, 18 Mar 1999 16:05:11 -0500
From: "Prentice, Margaret (NCI)" <prenticm@bprb.nci.nih.gov>
USA
------
National Institutes of Health, Bethesda, MD. has just renovated and reopened
their existing P-4 facility. It is intended for use on multi-drug-resistant
tuberculosis.
Also, I believe that Southern Research Institute in Frederick, MD. is in the
process of building a P-4 lab for biological warfare defense research and/or
vaccine development. This section is headed by Dave Franz and can be, I
assume,
confirmed by him.
--
Peg Prentice
Biologist, National Cancer Institute, NIH
Bethesda, MD, USA
