[3
Date: Thu, 18 Mar 1999 13:13:40 -0600
From: "Slomka,Marek" <marek.slomka@abbott.com>
UK
----
My former chief at the Central Public Health Laboratory (CPHL), Dr David
Brown, has advised on the current state of UK category 4 virology
fascilities:
Three P4 labs are presently functioning, namely at:
- CPHL [Central Public Health Laboratory (London),
- Centre for Applied Microbiology & Research (CAMR, Porton Down) and
- National Institute for Biological Standards & Control (NIBSC, Potters
Bar).
Two new P4 labs are also being built at:
- the National Institute for Medical Research (NIMR, London) and
- the Ministry of Defence facility at the Chemical & Biological Defence
Establishment (CBDE, Porton Down).
An occasional error made by both lay people and professionals (ie
scientists/medics) is to confuse the two institutes at Porton Down: Despite
their close proximity, CAMR and CBDE are separate organisations.
--
Marek J Slomka, PhD
Murex Biotech Ltd
Dartford
Kent DA1 5LR
UK
marek.slomka@abbott.com
